# Firebase Credentials Template

This file should contain your Firebase service account JSON.

## How to Get This File:

1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Select your project
3. Click the gear icon â†’ Project Settings
4. Go to "Service Accounts" tab
5. Click "Generate new private key"
6. Save the downloaded JSON as this file

## File Location:
- Save as: `config/firebase_credentials.json`
- This path is already in `.gitignore` (DO NOT commit to git)

## File Format:
The JSON should look like:
```json
{
  "type": "service_account",
  "project_id": "your-project-id",
  "private_key_id": "...",
  "private_key": "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n",
  "client_email": "firebase-adminsdk-...@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com",
  "client_id": "...",
  "auth_uri": "https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth",
  "token_uri": "https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token",
  "auth_provider_x509_cert_url": "https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/certs",
  "client_x509_cert_url": "..."
}
```

## Security Note:
This file contains sensitive credentials. Never commit it to git or share it publicly.
